This is ideal if you want something small enough for concealed carry but not too small for your hand- I have thick fingers and can fit my whole hand on the grips (awesome grips btw the gun feels just like an M&P but with better grips). 12+1 capacity, loaded chamber indicator, safety, adjustable sights, gun lock, Glock style takedown, very easy gun to use with plenty of features (including second strike capability- if for some reason the primer fails, just press the trigger again and it'll strike the primer a second time). First owner sent through mags through and I put another 200 through with no problems whatsoever. Cleaned thoroughly after each shooting (I'm very anal about keeping firearms clean), overall well taken care of firearm. Comes with case, two magazines full of self defense ammo (each has a different kind), snap caps so you can be extra sure the dry firing won't damage any mechanisms, two gun tools (for sight adjustment and locking the firearm), cleaning brush, owner manual, and transferable warranty card (Taurus has a transferable lifetime warranty). $290 or best offer takes it! Buyer covers transfer fees, thanks for looking and happy shooting- Dean REDACTED

The Daniel Defense M4 Carbine V11, based on the popular V9 series, was designed for shooters who prefer the benefits of the KeyMod system integrated in the new SLiM Rail™ (Slim Lightweight Modular).  KeyMod is a recoil resistant, two-part, direct attachment method for accessories that offers outstanding “return-to-zero” when accessories are removed and reinstalled.  The new SLiM Rail™ 15.0 offers incredible weight savings as well as superior cooling, ergonomics, and modularity while maintaining the strength and durability expected from Daniel Defense.  The long, 15” rail gives operators the option to have the support hand extended out closer to the muzzle allowing them to drive the gun more precisely and prevents over travel when transitioning between multiple targets.  This combined with our mid-length gas system, which is known to have a smoother recoil impulse, allows for quick, but precise rapid fire.  An uninterrupted picatinny rail on top and KeyMod attachment at 3, 6, and 9 o’clock, ensures plenty of real estate for optics and accessories and allows for maximum sight radius for accurate shooting with rail mounted iron sights.  The DDM4v11 is equipped with a free-floating, Cold Hammer Forged, 16” Government profile barrel and the newly designed, rugged and comfortable Daniel Defense Buttstock and Pistol grip.  This rifle is finished in Mil Spec+™ Cerakote™.

title: For Sale:  Tactical SKS
location: South Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
I have a tactical sks that is in great shape. It is in a tapco t6 tactical stock. I have 3 magazines for it (20 rounders "most reliable). Two tapco and a pro mag great condition. Also has a sling. It has an upgrade match grade trigger (not the clunky 8 pound pull original). It has a new buffer spring and a great bolt/carrier. This rifle shoots great and you will not find a better trigger. I am selling this as a package deal. It comes with a hard case, the rifle + sling, 3 magazines, and a long rifle stock made for the sks which can be used if you want to use the built in original sks magazine + stripper clips. The long rifle stock is not a cheap thin polymer. It is heavy and thick and feels great. If you add all of this up in which I paid for it:
Sks Gun $325
Tapco t6 stock $100
Long Rifle Comp $90
Tapco mag $20
tapco mag$ 20
pro mag $20
Case $30
sling $15
Match Grade trigger $140 (yes i paid 140 for it and i will let you dry fire it and you will see why, and no it is not a rip off. This is not a factory clunker)
New Buffer Spring $25
All of this comes up to 785 bucks. And I am asking 400. Gun is in great shape the metal has some blemishes due to age but no gouges and or damage. Barrel is in great shape and I only fire brass winchester. Yes you can call me a snob :). No Surplus/Corrosive ammo. I have gotten some grief over the trigger and its price but if you know anything about the old SKS and stiff trigger when you feel this you will know why I paid the price that I did. I am not in a rush to sell this and I think 400 bucks is a pretty awesome deal. This gun does not jam and it shoots clean. I have shot cheap tula through it before and it still shoots just as good although I dont like cheap ammo. Again I am a snob when it comes to my weapons and I take very good care of them and clean them well. I am looking to buy an Ak so I am selling this as I already own to other SKS. The recevier cover of this rifle does have a rail mount built in for a scope but I have never recomended scoping on the receiver cover. They dont stay zeroed in well and if you MUST scope you want to buy one you can mount in front of the bolt. If you do not like this rail cover you can buy an original for 40 bucks online. I like mine because i mount a pressure switched flash light which lights up the front and rear sights for night time shooting :D While this gun is not an AR or an AK I prefer it over my zavasta ak due to the fact it can shoot pass 150 yards. The only downsize to the SKS in my opnion is they are longer then the ak and hold 20 rounds. You can buy the 30 rounders but i like my vertical grip on it and it leaves more room with the 20s.

title: For Sale:  Career II 707
postcontent:
Selling My Air Rifle CAREER II 707 Very Hard to find,Like Brand New! With " Simmons 1048 M1 "Scope
Price $399 will take some trade's let me know what you got...

The Career 707 blew the doors off the PCP market when it was introduced in the US in the 1990s. Even after all these years, this airgun continues to be a favorite among hunters.

The variable power levels give you a huge range of energy for taking small- and medium-sized game at distances previously reserved only for firearms. The gun is manufactured by ShinSung, a Korean company that knows what hunters need and want, because Koreans have been using the Career far longer to hunt all types of game.

The Monte Carlo Indonesian hardwood stock has a raised cheekpiece and checkering on the wrist (directly above the lever). The forearm also has checkering to ensure a firm grip when you're in the thick of things. The lever-action cocking mechanism works quickly, smoothly and effortlessly as you chamber each pellet from the multi-shot magazine.

The number of shots you can load in the mag depends on the length of the pellets, but most people load about 6 pellets (although you can fit 10 Crosman Premiers!). Longer ones take up more room, so you won't be able to load as many. 

The built-in manometer (air pressure gauge) shows you how much air remains in the two built-in air reservoirs, located directly below the barrel. This air rifle was the first to offer adjustable velocities with its integral power wheel. Adjust the wheel to accommodate heavy or light pellets, long or short distances and the type of game you're shooting. The gun adjusts to YOUR needs instead of the other way around! Max velocity is 1,250 fps in .22 cal. and 1,000 fps in .25 cal. You'll get up to 20 full-power shots.

The two-stage trigger can be adjusted to your shooting preference. The front sight is a hunting-style ramp with a bead, and the rear sight is fully adjustable. The Career 707 is known for its accuracy.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Blueprinted Remington 700 - 6.5x284 - HS precison stock
postcontent:
For your consideration is a blueprinted Remington 700 chambered in a 6.5x284. The action has been squared and trued center to bore; the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore. The actions lugs have also been squared and trued. The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared. All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore. Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed.

For this build we used a Shilen match grade chrome barrel with a 1-8 twist rate. The contour is a "Sendero" contour which is a light bull barrel. The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action. The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015". This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter. The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown. I have plenty of pics to share showing the machine work being completed.

Once the machine work was completed and the rifle test fired the barreled action was given a caustic blue matte finish. This rifle can still be customized to your needs - spiral flute the bolt; add a muzzle brake; cerakote finish; detachable mag; ect.

Rifle is being offered with an HS precision "sendero" stock with a BDL trigger guard and the factory trigger adjusted to a crsip 3lbs. with zero creep. The BDL trigger guard and trigger are not in the pic because the BDL was being cerakoted...  This rifle will easily shoot 1/2 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/4 MOA using hand loaded ammo. I have other stocks that can be used for this build if you prefer a different color or style. I can even sell just the barreled action with trigger for 1200.  I will also include a set of RBCS 6.5x284 reloading dies with the complete rifle.

I have a few other blueprinted Rem 700s avalible as well so if you have another caliber in mind send a note... I probally have it or can build it.

Will ship to your FFL if needed.  As far as trading - any firearms I will consider...  worst I can say is no thanks.
